</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Architecture" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Built for an Edo era sake wholesaler, this traditional machiya and warehouse has a new life as the Shimadai Gallery.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_IMG_1038.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_IMG_1038.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Kyoto Marathon・京都マラソン</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250216/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Kyoto Marathon・京都マラソン" /><published>2025-02-16T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-02-16T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/kyoto-marathon</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250216/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
